% General rule: A person acquires British citizenship if they acquire it by any specific means
a person acquires British citizenship if
    the person acquires British citizenship by birth.

a person acquires British citizenship if
    the person acquires British citizenship by descent.

% General citizenship status rules
a person is a British citizen on a date if
    the person acquires British citizenship by birth
    and the person is born in the UK on the date.

a person is a British citizen on a date if
    the person acquires British citizenship by descent
