% Classification as British citizen by descent (Section 14)
a person is a British citizen by descent on a date if
    the person acquires British citizenship by descent
    and the person is born outside the UK on the date.

a person is a British citizen otherwise than by descent on a date if
    the person acquires British citizenship by birth
    and the person is born in the UK on the date.

